SIMPLE: emanation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emanation
<hw>Em`a*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emanatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧manation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of flowing or proceeding from a fountain head
or origin.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those profitable and excellent <qex>emanations</qex> from God.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which issues, flows, or proceeds from any
object as a source; efflux; an effluence; <as>as, perfume is an
<ex>emanation</ex> from a flower</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>emanation</qex> of the indwelling life.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emanative</ent>⟦br⟧
